{"TopicId":204121,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Weird shadows","CreatedByName":"AnFa","CreatedById":200695,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T02:50:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AnFa","CreatedById":200695,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T02:50:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I have this issue where the shadows look REALLY weird past a certain distance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ghkXj84.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022506\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ghkXj84.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFarther away\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pUz7sgV.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022506\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/pUz7sgV.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCloser.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this kind of thing normal? \u003Cspan\u003EHere are my GameData folder for my mods\u0027 list:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p1NR0lm.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002287.50\u0022 height=\u0022492\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/p1NR0lm.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd my graphics\u0027 options:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wPkIjpb.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022506\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wPkIjpb.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T03:12:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerfectly normal, the game reduces shadow resolution the further away something is from your viewpoint\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AnFa","CreatedById":200695,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T03:51:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224012583\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204121\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627701155\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208637\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrdinaryKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, OrdinaryKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerfectly normal, the game reduces shadow resolution the further away something is from your viewpoint\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo this degree? Also, is there a mod that improves that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T04:05:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224012596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204121\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627703511\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022200695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AnFa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, AnFa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo this degree? Also, is there a mod that improves that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\niirc\u00A0with Scatterer you can adjust the shadow cascade distance so you can see the higher-res shadows from further away, but I\u0027m not sure which line in scatterer config does that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-07-31T04:06:14Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2021 04:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by OrdinaryKerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AnFa","CreatedById":200695,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T04:06:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224012601\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204121\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627704317\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208637\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrdinaryKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, OrdinaryKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\niirc\u00A0with Scatterer you can adjust the shadow cascade distance so you can see the higher-res shadows from further away\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. It was what I did. I disabled SMAA in the scattering tab and just activated long distance shadows and left the standard values. Thank you for your help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-31T04:09:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224012602\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204121\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627704409\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022200695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AnFa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, AnFa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. It was what I did. I disabled SMAA in the scattering tab and just activated long distance shadows and left the standard values. Thank you for your help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSMAA doesn\u0027t affect shadows, it\u0027s the long-distance shadows (that enables Scatterer shadow settings overriding stock ones) so leave scatterer SMAA on (without it, you get pixelated edges when using Scatterer unless you have a TUFX or KS3P config with FXAA/SMAA/TAA on)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-07-31T04:11:44Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2021 04:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by OrdinaryKerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}